Summary: Our understanding of stellar pulsation, and RR Lyrae variables specifically, has seen exciting new discoveries from space-based data. We will use TESS data to examine the Fourier analysis of RR Lyrae lightcurves in detail, characterize these additional frequencies, find their ubiquity in a representative sample from the Galaxy, and search for any possible link to the Blazhko effect.
